{
  "doc_id": "13095",
  "text": "Mitochondrial lipid composition.-Total lipids were extracted from mitochondria (10 mg protein) using the Bligh and Dyer procedure [CITATION_1] . The extract was dried under a flow of n 2 and resuspended in a proper volume of CHCl 3 . To analyze fatty acids, liver mitochondria were saponified with ethanolic KOH for 2 hours at 90°C. Fatty acids were extracted [CITATION_2] , and their corresponding methyl esters (fatty acid methyl esters) were prepared by transesterification with 17% methanolic boron trifluoride (BF 3 ) at 65°C for 30 minutes. Fatty acid methyl esters were then analyzed by gasliquid chromatography [CITATION_3] . Peak identification was performed by using known standards, and relative quantitation was automatically carried out by peak integration.",
